{"id":5026,"date":"2012-08-12T13:42:58","date_gmt":"2012-08-12T17:42:58","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=5026"},"modified":"2025-03-16T16:15:24","modified_gmt":"2025-03-16T12:15:24","slug":"men-silk","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/12\/men-silk\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Silk: What can men do with silk?"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ibn Umar reported: Umar bought a silk cloak from the market and took it to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, saying, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, take it and wear it on Eid and when the delegations visit you.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>This clothing is for those who have no share in the Hereafter.<\/strong>\u201d After a while, the Prophet sent a silk cloak to Umar. Umar came to the Prophet with the cloak, saying, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, you said this clothing was for those who have no share in the Hereafter, yet you have sent me this cloak?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Sell it or take care of your needs with it<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>And the Prophet said, &#8220;<strong>Verily, I did not send it for you to wear it. Rather, I sent it for you to make veils out of it for your women<\/strong>.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 948, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2068<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0<\/strong><\/em>(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u200c\u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0623\u064e\u062e\u064e\u0630\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064f \u062c\u064f\u0628\u064e\u0651\u0629\u064b \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0625\u0650\u0633\u0652\u062a\u064e\u0628\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0642\u064d \u062a\u064f\u0628\u064e\u0627\u0639\u064f \u0641\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0633\u064f\u